This paper is about measuring and comparing the accuracy of interference models used in wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer science - networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of Rayleigh fading wireless channels, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions directional antennas and blockage, which are topics related to multimedia (cs.MM) and security and privacy (cs.SI), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the accuracy of interference models, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
